f=Cybersecurity/cortex/custom/security-incident-response/SKILL.md · in=mechanized response security incidents detection through containment, eradication, recovery, lessons. Combines **thiagofernandes1987 incident-response** (14 MITRE-mapped types, DFRWS forensics, regulatory notification), **Incident Commander** (runbook integration, communications, post-incident reviews), **aj-geddes Incident Response Plan** (structured containment/eradication/recovery playbooks). fleet-specific overlay enforces security-inversion (cortex detects/recommends, operator contains) hard boundary between security incidents (cortex) reliability incidents (ops). **Primary methodology:** thiagofernandes1987 incident-response (14-type MITRE mapping, DFRWS forensics, regulatory clocks). **Runbook/communications:** Incident Commander. **Recovery playbooks:** aj-geddes. **Fleet overlay:** custom. · p=security incident happens breach, compromise, data leak quality response determines damage. structured, pre-planned, well-practiced process reduces dwell time, limits blast radius, ensures evidence preserved forensics, meets regulatory notification clocks. Without it, response panicked, ad-hoc, expensive. · wu=security incident confirmed (SEV1/SEV2 security-monitoring triage)., "We've breached," "confirmed compromise," "ransomware," "data leak.", Tabletop exercise practice plan., Post-incident review lessons learned. · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| # \| Type \| MITRE ATT&CK \| Description \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 1 \| **Ransomware** \| T1486 \| Encrypting data for ransom \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 2 \| **Data Exfiltration** \| T1048 \| Unauthorized data transfer out \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 3 \| **Account Compromise** \| T1078 \| Credential theft or misuse \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 4 \| **Phishing / Social Engineering** \| T1566 \| Deceptive credential harvesting \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 5 \| **Malware Infection** \| T1204 \| Unauthorized software execution \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 6 \| **Insider Threat** \| T1529 \| Malicious or negligent internal actor \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 7 \| **DDoS** \| T1498 \| Availability attack \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 8 \| **Web Application Attack** \| T1190 \| Exploitation of web vulnerabilities \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 9 \| **Supply Chain / Third-Party Incident** \| T1195 \| Breach at a vendor or partner \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 10 \| **Physical Security Breach** \| T1056 \| Unauthorized physical access \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 11 \| **Policy Violation** \| — \| Internal policy breach (non-malicious) \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 12 \| **Unauthorized Access** \| T1078 \| Access without proper authorization \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 13 \| **Misconfiguration** \| T1562 \| Security control weakened by config error \| · h2:Classification Incident Types (thiagofernandes1987, MITRE ATT&CK mapped)=\| 14 \| **Unknown / Emerging Threat** \| — \| Novel pattern not matching above types \| · st:/ Protocol=`DETECTION (from security-monitoring triage — SEV1/SEV2 confirmed) \· → CLASSIFY incident type (14-type MITRE-mapped matrix) \· → CONTAIN (cortex recommends containment action → OPERATOR executes — the inversion) \· → INVESTIGATE (DFRWS six-phase forensics: identification → preservation → collection → examination → analysis → reporting) \· → ERADICATE (remove threat from environment — operator-executed)` · h3:Phase Classify (thiagofernandes1987)=**Identify incident type** 14-type MITRE-mapped matrix. one type apply (e.g., ransomware often involves data exfiltration). **Check false positive filters** (thiagofernandes1987): CI/CD agents, test environments, vulnerability scanners, known baseline behaviors. detection matches known benign pattern incident document rule tuning need. · h3:Phase Contain (fleet inversion)=**cortex recommends containment; operator executes.** cortex determines appropriate containment action: isolate host, revoke credentials, block IP, disable account. operator applies cortex sends recommendation, execute (the security-inversion). **Containment optional.** Even before full investigation, affected asset contained prevent lateral movement further data loss. · h3:Phase Investigate (DFRWS forensics thiagofernandes1987)=**DFRWS six-phase forensic framework:** · h3:Phase Investigate (DFRWS forensics thiagofernandes1987)=**Identification** what happened, what systems affected, what's scope, **Preservation** ensure evidence modified (memory capture, disk imaging, log保全), **Collection** gather relevant logs, system state, network flows, **Examination** analyze collected data indicators compromise, **Analysis** determine root cause, timeline, data accessed, **Reporting** document findings stakeholders potential legal/regulatory use · h3:Phase Eradicate Recover (aj-geddes operator)=**Eradication:** Remove threat environment malware removal, account revocation, backdoor closure. Operator-executed. **Recovery:** Restore affected systems known-good backups. Verify integrity before returning production. aj-geddes playbooks. · h3:Phase Notify (thiagofernandes1987 veil coordination)=**Regulatory notification clocks:** Check applicable obligations incident type: · h3:Phase Notify (thiagofernandes1987 veil coordination)=**GDPR**: hours awareness, **PCI-DSS**: hours cardholder data incidents, **HIPAA**: days (or sooner depending scope), **Coordinate veil's breach-notification skill** jurisdiction-specific obligations. · h3:Phase Post-Incident (Incident Commander)=**Post-incident review:** Timeline reconstruction, communication log, what went well, what went wrong, action items owners due dates. 10. **Lessons warden:** incident produces lessons update risk register improve controls. repeat incident process failure. · of=`## Incident Response: [incident ID] — [type per 14-type matrix] \· Severity: [SEV1/SEV2] \· Status: [contained / investigating / eradicated / recovered / closed] \· MITRE ATT&CK: [technique IDs] \· Containment: [action recommended → operator executed: y/n] \· Forensics (DFRWS): [phase \· key findings]` · pr=**Contain first, investigate second** limit blast radius before root cause analysis., **cortex recommends; operator contains** security-inversion holds crisis., **Evidence preservation before remediation** don't clean before forensics., **Regulatory clocks start awareness** notification obligations tracked first confirmation., **Post-incident review mandatory** SEV1/SEV2 closes without lessons., **Security incidents (cortex) reliability incidents (ops)** ransomware both; joint IR, cortex leads eradication/forensics, ops leads recovery. · f=forensics tools available document findings preservation steps manually; flag gap warden., Regulatory obligation unknown flag "[REGULATORY CLOCK] check jurisdiction" escalate operator., Joint incident ops (outage breach) establish joint command: ops leads service recovery, cortex leads threat eradication/forensics., Tabletop exercise mode simulated incident production action; walk through classification containment recommendation investigation notification review. · b:with Other Skills=**security-monitoring** (sibling): triage queue feeds SEV1/SEV2 skill full IR., **threat-hunting** (sibling): threat hunts directly discover active compromise, bypassing monitoring triage., **detection-engineering** (sibling): findings trigger new detection rules tuning., **veil's breach-notification** (Cybersecurity): coordinates regulatory notification clocks jurisdiction., **ops (Engineering)**: joint security+reliability incidents use process; ops leads recovery, cortex leads forensics., **warden**: incident lessons register entries; repeat incidents indicate control failures., **board (Governance)**: material security incidents (data breach, regulatory fine risk) escalate board risk-acceptance threshold.